# Implement Email Verification System

This plan describes how to build a production-level email verification system. Users will not be able to log in until they click a secure link sent to their email.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Since we are adding an `isVerified` field to the User schema, **all existing users in your database will not be able to log in** unless we either:
> 1. Manually update existing users in MongoDB to `isVerified: true`.
> 2. Create a script to do it for you.
> For new users, the flow will work perfectly.

## Proposed Changes

### MongoDB Schema

#### [MODIFY] [src/model/user.model.js](file:///c:/Java-Script/projects/skytrack/Backend/src/model/user.model.js)
- Add `isVerified` boolean field, defaulting to `false`.
- Add `verificationToken` string field.
- Add `verificationTokenExpiresAt` date field to limit how long a link is valid (e.g., 24 hours).

### Email Utility

#### [NEW/MODIFY] [src/utils/emailService.js](file:///c:/Java-Script/projects/skytrack/Backend/src/utils/emailService.js) (Recreated)
- Recreate the Nodemailer transporter (since it was accidentally deleted in the previous action).
- Add a new `sendVerificationEmail(userEmail, userName, verificationUrl)` function with a professional, secure HTML template containing the verification link.
- Restore the `sendWelcomeEmail` and `sendBookingConfirmationEmail` functions.

### Controllers & Routes

#### [MODIFY] [src/controller/user.controller.js](file:///c:/Java-Script/projects/skytrack/Backend/src/controller/user.controller.js)
- **In [signupUser](file:///c:/Java-Script/projects/skytrack/Backend/src/controller/user.controller.js#24-67)**: 
  - Generate a secure random crypto token.
  - Set `isVerified=false` and save the token/expiration to the database.
  - Call the new email service to send the `http://localhost:5000/api/users/verify-email/:token` link instead of the standard welcome email. (We can send the welcome email *after* verification).
- **In [loginUser](file:///c:/Java-Script/projects/skytrack/Backend/src/controller/user.controller.js#68-111)**:
  - Before checking passwords, check if `user.isVerified === true`.
  - If false, return a `403 Forbidden` structured message: "Please verify your email first to login."
- **[NEW] `verifyEmail` controller**:
  - Accept a token from the URL params.
  - Find the user who has that exact token and where the expiration date is still in the future.
  - If valid, set `isVerified=true`, clear the token fields, and save.
  - Redirect the user to the frontend login page or return a success JSON message.

#### [MODIFY] `src/routes/user.routes.js`
- Add the `GET /verify-email/:token` route pointing to the `verifyEmail` controller.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Attempt to sign up with a new user. Verify the database sets `isVerified: false` and generates a token.
2. Attempt to log in with that new user immediately. Verify it fails with the "Please verify your email first" message.
3. Check the user's email inbox, click the verification link.
4. Attempt to log in again. Verify it succeeds and generates a JWT token.
